dfl860ePipeUsers.name: dfl860ePipeUsers
dfl860ePipeUsers.description: The current number of users, as defined by the grouping settings of each pipe, being tracked in the pipes system. Note that this value corresponds to the number of users active in each time slice of 1/20th of a second, and not to the number of users having open connections.

dfl860ePipeEntry.description: A entry of the pipes table

dfl860ePipeDefPrec.name: dfl860ePipeDefPrec
dfl860ePipeDefPrec.description: The precedence assigned to a packet for which has not one allready done by a Pipe Rule.

dfl860ePipeNumUsers.name: dfl860ePipeNumUsers
dfl860ePipeNumUsers.description: The current number of users, as defined by the grouping settings of each pipe, being tracked in the pipes system. This value corresponds to the number of users active in each time slice and not to the number of users having open connections.

dfl860ePipeCurrentBps.name: dfl860ePipeCurrentBps
dfl860ePipeCurrentBps.description: The current throughput of a pipe, in bits per second, as a sum of the corresponding values for all precedences.

dfl860ePipeCurrentPps.name: dfl860ePipeCurrentPps
dfl860ePipeCurrentPps.description: The current throughput of a pipe, in packets per second, as a sum of the corresponding values for all precedences.

dfl860ePipeDelayedPackets.name: dfl860ePipeDelayedPackets
dfl860ePipeDelayedPackets.description: The number of times packets have been delayed as a result of a pipe, or pipe user having used up its allotted bandwidth. Note that one single packet may be delayed several times; if a pipe is really full, this count may exceed the number of packets actually passing through the pipe.

dfl860ePipeDropedPackets.name: dfl860ePipeDropedPackets
dfl860ePipeDropedPackets.description: The number of packets dropped by a pipe. Packets are dropped when CorePlus is running out of packet buffers. This occurs when excessive amounts of packets need to be queued for later delivery. The packet dropped is always the one that has been queued the longest time globally, which means that the connection suffering from packet loss will be the one most overloading the system.

dfl860ePipePrecTable.name: dfl860ePipePrecTable
dfl860ePipePrecTable.description: There is a one to many relation between a pipe and its precedences. The number of precedences is a instance attribute of each pipe. This table extends the pipes table in order to express the relation between a pipe and the respective precedences.

dfl860ePipePrecEntry.name: dfl860ePipePrecEntry
dfl860ePipePrecEntry.description: An entry of the table of pipe pecedences. These table entries are chracterized by been indexed by two values. The first index the same as the pipe index of the corresponding row in table of pipes and the second index is the index of the set of precedences of the corresponding pipe.

dfl860ePipePrecIndex.name: dfl860ePipePrecIndex
dfl860ePipePrecIndex.description: Index of a precedence of a specific pipe. This is the second index of the entries of pipe precedence table described by object dfl860ePipePrecEntry.

dfl860ePipePrecBps.name: dfl860ePipePrecBps
dfl860ePipePrecBps.description: The current throughput of the pipe, in bits per second, with the corresponding precedence.

dfl860ePipePrecTotalPps.name: dfl860ePipePrecTotalPps
dfl860ePipePrecTotalPps.description: The current throughput of the pipe precedence, in packets per second.

dfl860ePipePrecReservedBps.name: dfl860ePipePrecReservedBps
dfl860ePipePrecReservedBps.description: The current bandwidth allocated to the precedence.

dfl860ePipePrecDynLimBps.name: dfl860ePipePrecDynLimBps
dfl860ePipePrecDynLimBps.description: The current bandwidth limit limit applied the precedence.

dfl860ePipePrecDynUsrLimBps.name: dfl860ePipePrecDynUsrLimBps
dfl860ePipePrecDynUsrLimBps.description: The current precedence bandwidth limit per user of the pipe.

dfl860ePipePrecDelayedPackets.name: dfl860ePipePrecDelayedPackets
dfl860ePipePrecDelayedPackets.description: The number of times packets have been delayed as a result of a precedence, or pipe user having used up its allotted bandwidth. Note that one single packet may be delayed several times; if a pipe is really full, this count may exceed the number of packets of this precedence actually passing through the pipe.

dfl860ePipePrecDropedPackets.name: dfl860ePipePrecDropedPackets
dfl860ePipePrecDropedPackets.description: The number of pipe dropped packets with the corresponding precedence.
